metatags.og:title: Tip for Getting More Organized:  Don't
metatags.og:description: How much time do you spend each day getting better organized? Cut it in half. When it comes to investing time, thought and effort into productively organizing oneself, less is more. In fact, not only is less more, research suggests it may be faster, better and cheaper. IBM researchers observed that email users who "searched" rather than set up files and folders for their correspondence typically found what they were looking for faster and with...
